String manipulation:

indexOf()
	returns the position of the first occurrence of a specified value in a string.
	
	var str = "Hello world, welcome to the universe.";
	var n = str.indexOf("welcome"); //13

String length: length
	returns the number of characters in a string
	
	var str = "Hello World!";
	var n = str.length; //12
	
Size of Objects:
	var size = Object.keys(myObj).length;
	
Extract a substring from a string:
	var str = "Hello world!";
	var res = str.substring(1, 4); //ell
	
Number to String:
	var num=213; 
    var n = num.toString(); //213

Sort array of strings:
	var array1 = ["Ba", "Oo", "Aa"];
	array1.sort(); //Aa Ba Oo
	
Reverse the order of elements in a string array:
	var array1 = ["Ba", "Oo", "Aa"];
	array1.reverse(); //Aa Oo Ba
	
Slice out a part of the original array:
	var arr = [23,56,87,32,75,13];
	var new_arr = arr.slice(2,4);	//87, 32

looping through an array:
	someValues.forEach((element, index) => {
		console.log("index: "+ index);
		console.log("element: " + element);
	});
	
performance measurement:
	var entireStart = performance.now();
	var entireFinish = performance.now();
	console.log("Completion time: " + (entireFinish - entireStart));
	
return random number up to max-1:
	Math.floor(Math.random() * Math.floor(max))